Sonangol Pesquisa e Producao to Raise Production, Angop Says

-- B y   H e n r i q u e   A l m e i d a
-- 
2011-08-30T10:06:47Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-30/sonangol-pesquisa-e-producao-to-raise-production-angop-says.html
Sonangol Pesquisa e Producao SA, the
research and exploration unit of Angolan state-oil company
Sonangol SA, will boost production in coming years,  Agencia
Angola Press  said, citing Joao Gaspar, director of operations.  The company expects oil reserves to increase and it will
raise production to sustain expansion abroad, Gaspar said,
according to the state-owned  news agency . The report didn’t say
by how much output would expand. Sonangol Pesquisa e Producao
currently produces 1,000 barrels of oil a day.  The company has entered into partnerships with companies in
 Africa  and oil producing countries in the Gulf of Guinea, Gabon,
 Equatorial Guinea , Nigeria and Sao Tome to help promote and
develop exploration in Africa, Angola Press said.  Angola is Africa’s biggest oil producer after Nigeria.  To contact the reporter responsible for this story:
Henrique Almeida at   halmeida5@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
